subsection.content:
A certificate issued pursuant to a request under subsection (1) and containing
                a statement that it has been so issued has effect for the purposes of this Part as
                if the certificate had been issued by the relevant government. (Added 10 of 2009 s. 12 and E.R. 5 of 2021)

section.def:
e-cert database (電子證書資料庫), in relation to a certifying authority, means an electronic
            database that is maintained or managed by or for the certifying authority in accordance
            with the e-cert guidelines;

e-cert guidelines (電子證書指引) means the documents listed in Division 1 of Part 3 of the
                Schedule, as from time to time revised or amended by revisions or
            amendments to those documents;

e-log guidelines (電子航海日誌指引) means the documents listed in Division 2 of Part 3 of
            the Schedule, as from time to time revised or amended by revisions or
            amendments to those documents;

